voice_to_text: The scene before Anna sent her into an immediate panic. Though the appearance of her friend brought some slight relief to her anxiety, the situation only worsened. Another friend was now trapped in an even more horrifying device. Suddenly, the kidnapper's voice crackled through the television on the wall, announcing that the device would activate in 60 seconds and offering a cryptic clue about the keys location. A box then appeared, and when Anna opened it, she found nothing but a small knife inside. Paralyzed with indecision, she couldn't bring herself to harm either herself or her friend. The kidnapper's voice cut through the silence. Key is in your eye. Terrified, Anna had no choice but to obey. Mercifully, it was only a glass eye, and she successfully extracted the key, disabling the device at the very last moment. Just then, Jack's two children were lowered from above, dangling over a terrifying device that had already been activated. Children began descending rapidly and Jack desperately grabbed the other end. But a new device emerged beneath him, starting to attack him. His mind raced with uncertainty, unable to predict what horror the mechanism would unleash. Suddenly, two devices rose beneath Jack's feet and a countdown began, 60 seconds to choose between saving himself or saving his children. In the end, he made his decision without hesitation.

voice_to_text: Amon accidentally discovers that pregnancy can awaken a coma patient, someone he deeply loves. Determined, he decides to do whatever it takes. By the time the hospital found out, Annie had missed three months of her period and her belly had a slight curve. An emergency meeting was convened to discuss the unusual situation. Afterward, everyone believed it was George, as he had been the one taking care of Anne. His colleagues defended him, mentioning that he often filled in for others, which seemed perfectly reasonable. But soon they realized that during a colleague's illness, George had stepped in and even forged Annie's menstrual records. What shocked everyone most was that George didn't defend himself at all. Six months later, George's friend Jack uncovered the full story. He hurried back from another city to confront him, and the first thing he asked was why George had done it. But George showed no remorse. He pleaded with Jack to check on Annie's condition. Reluctantly, Jack agreed, knowing he had nowhere else to stay, and George offered him a place at his house. As Jack entered George's home, he noticed a photo of Annie on the wall. Walking towards the window, he suddenly spotted a familiar figure. Looking closer, he realized it was Annie. It turned out George's actions had worked. The pregnancy stimulus had helped Annie regain consciousness. She was now undergoing rehabilitation.

voice_to_text: The monster's carcass was towed away by an aircraft carrier. Humanity had paid a terrible price. Six cities were reduced to ashes. Tens of millions ascended to heaven. Yet barely a month later, a second creature struck again. No one knew how it came to be, only that it rose suddenly from the depths of the Pacific. Its island sized claws tore apart every bridge that spanned the seas. The military deployed every force available and it took 15 long days to bring this monster down. But before the world could celebrate, a third and a fourth appeared in succession. At that moment, nations around the globe united as never before. They pooled the finest technologies on earth and forged humanity's ultimate weapon. The Jaeger warriors. Mankind's vengeance had begun. With these steel titans joining the fight, monsters across the world fell one after another. Confidence surged among humanity. But as even stronger beasts emerged, the Mighty Yeagers were destroyed one by one. And those precious pilots drew fewer with every battle. Jaegers could be rebuilt, but pilots could not, because each one required an extraordinary level of strength and endurance. I was once an elite Jaeger pilot. But 10 years ago, in a battle against a beast, I watched helplessly as my brother was slain before my eyes, powerless to save him. Since that day, guilt has consumed me. My brother's death is a wound I can never heal. But now, with humanity's fate hanging between life and death, Personal pain no longer matters. Soon I arrived at humanity's last Jaeger base. The remaining four combat mechs had become our final hope. The first was China's Crimson Typhoon, piloted by triplet brothers who had defended Hong Kong 10 times. Second was Russia's Chernobyl Alpha, which held the Siberian border for five relentless years, manned by a battlehardened husband and wife. The third was Australia's striker Eureka, the fastest Jaeger in the world, piloted by a father and son team. And the fourth, the mightiest of them all, was Gypsy Danger. Nearly destroyed in that war ten years ago, I barely managed to bring her back to shore, allowing humanity to rebuild her. voice_to_text: For 30 long years, Sam lived like a king inside a magnificent villa. Not because of his own success, but simply because his girlfriend, Mary, was a billionaire. Every morning, Sam would wake up, stare into the mirror, and wonder, is Mary still alive? Deep down, he hoped that one day heaven would finally call her away so that all her fortune would become his. But once again, she was alive. Which meant the party wasn't over yet. And what a party it was. This wasn't just any house. The villa stretched across 3,000 square meters. Sam didn't just walk through it. He roamed freely. Thirty luxury cars stood lined up, one for every single day of the month. If coffee spilled, no problem. The servants rushed instantly. If he wanted to read while showering, maids turned the pages for him. If the sun hurt his eyes, the staff rotated his chair. It was total luxury. That day was special. Their 30th anniversary. Mary gifted Sam a priceless luxury watch. He put on an expression of deep emotion. But in truth, he didn't even remember the date. When he realized his mistake, he decided to buy her something, too. He went straight to a showroom, picked out a sleek sports car. But then another thought struck him. Mary couldn't even drive anymore. So he acted clever. I was going to buy this for you. But you won't be able to drive it. Mary believed him. She bought the car herself. Then immediately gifted it back to him. Just like always, Sam walked away clean. But luck doesn't last forever. When he reached home, he saw another identical sports car parked at the gate. And inside, a shocking surprise awaited. Mary had started a new relationship with the young car salesman. And now he was the one living in the villa. Sam stormed inside in rage, but the guards threw him out onto the street. No car, no status, no money. Being the boyfriend of a rich woman.

voice_to_text: To uncover the truth about whether ghosts and spirits truly exist, a daring woman made a shocking decision. She climbed into her grandfather's coffin with a camera in her hand. She even asked her younger brother to seal the coffin completely with wooden board. In an instant, the tomb was swallowed by absolute darkness. Annie switched on her camera, turned on the night vision mode, and prepared to document whatever might happen next. According to old legends, those who committed sins in life would face divine punishment after death. But Annie was determined to challenge that belief. She stayed in the coffin for two long days, yet the lifeless body beside her remained perfectly still. Just as the experiment was about to end, Annie decided to take a short rest, when suddenly an invisible force gripped her throat. Her breathing turned shallow and fast. Panicking, she cried out her brother's name, but he was outside the tomb, quietly smoking a cigarette. Completely unaware of her scream, Annie lifted her gaze toward the small air vent, only to see a snake sliding inside. Her pulse quickened every muscle in her body tent. The snake crept closer, but instead of attacking, turned away, crawling slowly across the corpse beside her and finally slithering into its mouth. Trembling, Annie raised her camera toward the body, hands shaking uncontrollably. Then, out of the suffocating silence came a strange guttural sound. And what followed next was something she would never forget.

The cracked screen repaired itself, and even the cut on his hand healed as if touched by magic. Jack quickly suspected the lake had mysterious power. To test his theory, he gathered all the broken items from home and carried them to the shore. When he returned, every single object looked brand new. The lake truly possessed miraculous healing energy. That night, a wild thought struck him. What if the lake could bring his mother back to life? While the whole house slept, Jack secretly carried his mother's urn to the lake. He didn't realize his sister Lisa was quietly following behind. At the water's edge, Lisa saw him lifting the urn and ran forward in horror to stop him. During their struggle, her sketchbook slipped from her hands and fell into the water. Jack hurried to fish it out with a branch, but then bubbles began to rise from the surface. Sensing something unnatural, he grabbed Lisa and pulled her away. Moments later, the lake roared and churned violently, as if something beneath was awakening. The next morning, their father came to wake the kids as usual. But Jack and Lisa were already up. And in Lisa's eyes there seemed to flicker the shadows of lingering spirit.

voice_to_text: He received another female corpse that night. As always, he insisted on preparing the body himself. To him, even in death, a person deserved to keep their final trace of dignity. But this time something was different. No matter what he did, the woman's eyes refused to close wide open, staring into nothing as though she were seeing something beyond this world. He didn't panic. Instead, he calmly reached for a small bottle of clear glue. A few seconds later he brushed a thin layer across her eyelid and slowly her eyes came to rest. Next he pick the foundation, carefully layering it across her pale skin until a faint, life like blush returned to her cheek. From the drawer, he pulled out an old yellowed coin and placed it gently upon her forehead, murmuring an ancient charm under his breath. When the ritual was done, his apprentice entered, ready to wheel the body into the morgue. He sat down, lit a cigarette, and let the smoke drift through the still air. Just as he began to relax, the apprentice pushed in another covered stretcher, urging him to get back to work. With a weary sigh, he rubbed his eyes and stood. The moment he lifted the white sheet, the air grew cold, and beneath it lay the face of a girl who had vanished 11 years ago.

voice_to_text: Mary never allows her husband to touch her in bed at night because whenever they make the slightest movement, the springs of the bed creek loudly. The noise not only disturbs them, but can also be heard by everyone in the entire building. To improve their married life, the next day while her husband is out, Mary goes to her male neighbor, a clown at a circus, and asks him to crawl under the bed to repair the springs. But with the bed still, the clown can't figure out what's wrong, so he asks Mary to sit on the bed and shake her body to make the springs move. Soon the bed starts shaking, but the clown still can't identify the problem. Mary thinks maybe her weight isn't enough, as the springs only make noise when her husband is on top of her. She invites the clown to sit on the bed with her and they shake it together to better figure out the issue. Without a second thought, the clown sits beside Mary and they begin shaking the bed, sinking it down. This sensation makes Mary feel something strange and her body starts to heat up in inexplicably. Sure enough, after shaking the bed for a while, the clown quickly finds the problem based on the different rhythms. He pulls out an oil can, pour some oil on the springs, and fixes the issue. Mary is very grateful to him. However, just as the clown is about to leave, Mary notices that the children from the upstairs neighbor's house have used a hook to snatch the clothes she hung out to dry and are playing with them.

voice_to_text: The lady of the house sampled the dinner, while the maid standing to her remained frozen in fear, for the entire family was hiding under the dining table. Fortunately, after dinner, the lady went upstairs and the maid quietly urged her family to sneak out while they still had the chance. Suddenly, the homeowner's daughter appeared at the foot of the stairs. Turned out, the little girl wanted to camp on the lawn that night. At that moment, the hidden family quickly crawled under the sofa, barely avoiding detection by the wealthy household. A new challenge lay ahead for them. How could they escape now? The daughter had comfortably settled in her tent outside, while the rich couple relaxed on the living room sofa beneath them. Hidden family held their breath, daring not to make a sound. Once the couple finally drifted off to sleep, the family carefully slid out from under the sofa, tiptoed toward the garage, slipped out through the back door of the villa. As the saying goes, a heavy rain exposes the true gap between the rich and the poor. The wealthier you are, the higher you live. While the poor family descended downhill, carried along like debris toward the depth of the city's drainage system. When they finally returned home, the shock was overwhelming. Their modest basement home had been destroyed.

The youngest snake quickly emerged from the floor drain, its fangs sinking into a woman's ankle. In an instant, the entire bathhouse was filled with a palpable sense of danger. The other women screamed in panic, rushing out of the bathroom. The woman who had just been enjoying a massage was already covered in snake bites. Anna, holding her daughter, rushed to the bathroom door, only to see chaos erupting in the men's room as well. With no other choice, Anna retreated with her daughter back into the bathroom. The two of them quickly hid inside a metal wardrobe. The snake slithered through the wardrobe's ventilation holes, biting and killing a female worker who had hidden inside. Soon, another snake slithered into the wardrobe, its tongue almost touching Anna's face. In a surge of terror, Anna suddenly pushed the wardrobe open, flinging the snake outside.
